INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (178,1,'2020-12-11 15:12:55','2020-12-11 15:12:55','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><strong>HEALTH MONITORING SYSTEM</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"dropCap\":true} -->\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap\">In today world of technology, application of engineering&nbsp;has proved its significance in the field of biomedical. It not only made doctor more efficient but also helped them in improving total process of medication. In multispecialty hospitals, where there are a huge number of wards and in each ward there is huge numbers&nbsp;of patients, doctors cannot handle&nbsp;the patient each and every moment. For this doctors form the time slots and each ward is visited after specific time difference. But patients may have some problems in between these time slots.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:more -->\n<!--more-->\n<!-- /wp:more -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":175,\"width\":441,\"height\":293,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://subhamkumar.local/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/6bf1c033684dd795d3433f24d3374e21.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-175\" width=\"441\" height=\"293\"/><figcaption>Fig:-Health Monitoring Device  With Wireless Sensors.</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The project aims at developing a patient monitoring system. The system contains an ECG simulator to generate ECG waveform. The ECG simulator has control to vary heart rate as well as to generate different types of arrhythmias.The monitoring system keeps track of the heart rate activity.The ECG simulator is designed using an oscillator and pulse shaping circuit.This leads to inconveniency of patient and hospital management may feel helplessness about the problem.The Patient monitoring system for doctors provides solution for this. It continuously providesheartbeat,body temperature,pulse rate and many informations to the doctor.A continuous monitoring of some basic crucial signs will be implemented.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Such asystem may support the specialist or individuals to monitor emergency alarms from the patients.In this project,we consider three parameters essential signs which are Pulse rate,Human bodytemperature and ECG.The data helps in protecting the patientslife.A micro controller is usedfor Analyzing the vitals parameters from the patient and any abnormality felt by the sensor alertsthe doctor and sends automated SMS to the specialists.This Project would benefit the patientbecause the patient can now not be confined to the single bed because the sensors are wearablenor any assistant doctor or nurse are required to logthe health vitals of the patient manually soreducing any attainable human error.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> The monitoring system keeps track of the heart rate activity.The ECG simulator is designed using an oscillator and pulse shaping circuit. The monitoring system contains an 8-bit ADC, 8-bit microcontroller and a GSM modem. The GSM modem is serially interfaced with the microcontroller. Standard AT command set is used to control GSM modem.Cost reduction pressures and the need for shortened in-patient stays are promoting the use of wireless patient monitoring systems in hospitals..Attracted by the many clinical and economic benefits of this technology, including its ability to relieve health authorities of huge cost pressures,&nbsp;Germany, France and the U.K. have emerged as early adopters of wireless networking in hospitals.The deployment of wireless systems involves several technical considerations that might prove expensive for hospitals.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','','','inherit','closed','closed','','172-revision-v1','','','2020-12-11 15:12:55','2020-12-11 15:12:55','',172,'http://subhamkumar.local/172-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
