INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (250,1,'2020-12-12 10:58:07','2020-12-12 10:58:07','<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"dropCap\":true} -->\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap\">In today world of technology,application of engineering has proved its significance in the field of biomedical. It not only made doctor more efficient but also helped them in improving total process of medication.In multispecialty hospitals, where there are a huge number of wards and in each ward there is huge numbers of patients, doctors cannot handle the patient each and every moment. For this doctors form the time slots and each ward is visited after specific time difference. But patients may have some problems in between these time slots. This leads to inconveniency of patient and hospital management may feel helplessness about the problem.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:more -->\n<!--more-->\n<!-- /wp:more -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Patient monitoring system for doctors provides solution for this. It continuously provides heartbeat,body temperature,pulse rate and many informations to the doctor.A continuous monitoring of some basic crucial signs will be implemented.Such a system may support the specialist or individuals to monitor emergency alarms from the patients.In this project,we consider three parameters essential signs which are Pulse rate,Human body temperature and ECG.The data helps in protecting the patientslife.A micro controller is used for Analyzing the vitals parameters from the patient and any abnormality felt by the sensor alerts the doctor and sends automated SMS to the specialists.This Project would benefit the patient because the patient can now not be confined to the single bed because the sensors are wearable nor any assistant doctor or nurse are required to log the health vitals of the patient manually so reducing any attainable human error.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":198,\"width\":368,\"height\":430,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://subhamkumar.local/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Digital-Finger-Pulse-Oximeter-Spo2h-SDL248292861-1-de64d.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-198\" width=\"368\" height=\"430\"/><figcaption>Fig:-Pulse Oximeter</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We have created a device that measures the ECG,Heart rate ,Temperature through various types of sensors which are connected through the zigbee wireless network.If any abnormality is detected by the sensors it triggers an emergency message to doctor and can help in saving patient life. In the extension of this project we have added a very new feature to it.this device can now measure the Blood saturation level of the patient using the MAX30001 sensor module which is interfaced with Arduino. Blood saturation measures the amount of oxygen present in the blood.This vital parameter has become the most used right now.Right now the world is suffering a massive pandemic that has literally shut down the whole world.This device can measure SPO2 which can indicate a serious case of COVID-19 and filter out the patient who can have potential serious case of COVID-19 and can help save them. 5Attracted by the many clinical and economic benefits of this technology, including its ability to relieve health authorities of huge cost pressures, Germany, France and the U.K. have emerged as early adopters of wireless networking in hospitals.The deployment of wireless systems involves several technical considerations that might prove expensive for hospital.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','HEALTH MONITORING DEVICE USING PULSE OXIMETRY','','inherit','closed','closed','','196-revision-v1','','','2020-12-12 10:58:07','2020-12-12 10:58:07','',196,'http://subhamkumar.local/196-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
